  "prompt": "What does RFP stand for in healthcare?",
  "response": "In the healthcare industry, RFP stands for \"Request for Proposal.\" It is a formal document that organizations use to solicit proposals from vendors or service providers for specific projects or services. The RFP process typically involves outlining the organization's requirements and expectations, allowing vendors to submit detailed proposals that demonstrate how they can meet those needs. This helps healthcare organizations evaluate different options and select the best partner for their project or service needs.",
